@October 20, 1999
       I was trying to get the gold cups in as few days as possible

   1  buy car GTO'92 Fiji blue GTO'92SR, med stab  Cr10,000 -> Cr240

       I thought I would start with the 4wd car since that is the
       only specialized category car you cannot guarantee to win:
       Demio is Lwt and FF, while various are FR (though I find it
       easiest to use the stock Viper used for the Normal Series).
       However, later I realized you pretty much want to buy a 4wd 
       GTO or a Skyline to win Tuned and All-Night 2, so the starter
       car might as well be as cheap as possibly with a reasonable
       probability of getting Sunday Cup poles after light tuning.
       This GTO'92 will only be a reasonable investment if I win
       the Supra in the Normal Series, which I can then use instead
       of a GTO.   (The GTO'92 could then win the 4wd series, with
       light tuning).  But it is more probable to win the Impreza,
       and, although it could be used in the 4wd, it makes more
       sense to buy a Japanese monster at that point anyway, so that
       monster might as well be 4wd.

